                        <h5>1. User Authentication and Session Management</h5>
                        <p>The platform includes a robust authentication system
                          that ensures secure and seamless user experiences:</p>
                        <ul>
                          <li><strong>Registration</strong>: Users can register
                            with their first name, last name, username, email,
                            and password. Passwords are hashed using bcrypt with
                            a salt factor of 10 for enhanced security. The
                            system checks for duplicate usernames or emails to
                            prevent conflicts.</li>
                          <li><strong>Login</strong>: Supports email and
                            password login with a “Remember Me” feature using
                            JWT, storing a 30-day token in an HTTP-only cookie
                            for auto-login. Session data is stored in MongoDB
                            using connect-mongo for persistence.</li>
                          <li><strong>Logout</strong>: Clears sessions and
                            cookies, redirecting users to the login page.</li>
                          <li><strong>Security</strong>: Middleware ensures
                            protected routes (e.g., admin dashboard) are
                            accessible only to authenticated users, with admin
                            privileges verified via a database flag (isAdmin).</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h5>2. Admin Dashboard with Analytics</h5>
                        <p>The admin dashboard, accessible at /admin, is a
                          powerful tool for managing content and analyzing user
                          engagement, tailored specifically for admin users:</p>
                        <ul>
                          <li><strong>User-Specific Metrics</strong>: Displays
                            the total number of registered users. Shows the
                            logged-in user’s post count, total views on their
                            posts, and comments received on their posts.
                            Calculates the average views per post for the
                            logged-in user.</li>
                          <li><strong>Monthly Views Chart</strong>: A dynamic
                            line chart, powered by Chart.js, visualizes monthly
                            view counts for the user’s posts over the past 12
                            months, aggregated using MongoDB’s pipeline for
                            efficient data processing.</li>
                          <li><strong>Design</strong>: Styled with SB Admin 2
                            and Bootstrap 5, the dashboard features responsive
                            cards with icons (Font Awesome) and a clean,
                            data-driven layout for quick insights.</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h5>3. Content Management</h5>
                        <p>The platform supports rich content management through
                          well-defined MongoDB schemas:</p>
                        <ul>
                          <li><strong>Posts</strong>: Users can create posts
                            with titles, slugs, content, categories, thumbnails,
                            tags, and a status (published or draft). Posts
                            support comments and track view counts.</li>
                          <li><strong>Categories</strong>: Categories organize
                            posts, with each category linked to multiple posts,
                            and the sidebar displays post counts per category.</li>
                          <li><strong>Comments</strong>: Comments are tied to
                            posts and users, with support for replies, enabling
                            threaded discussions.</li>
                          <li><strong>Admin Routes</strong>: Dedicated routes
                            (/admin/posts, /admin/category, /admin/comments)
                            allow admins to manage content efficiently, with
                            pagination and sorting for scalability.</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h5>4. Dynamic Sidebar Widgets</h5>
